E(X) = E(X^+) - E(X^-)
(\Omega, \mathcal{F}, P)
X \ge 0
\int^\infty_0 P(X > t) \, dt
 \int_{\Omega} X dP = \int_\Omega \int_0^\infty \mathbf{1}_{\{X > t\}} dt  \, d P 
 E(X) = \int_{\Omega} X dP = \int_\Omega \int_0^\infty \mathbf{1}_{\{X > t\}} dt  \, d P = \int_{0}^\infty P(X > t) dt. 
\int_\Omega X dP
E(X)
 E( X ) = E( \int_{0}^X dt ) = E( \int_0^\infty 1_{t < X} dt ) =  \int_0^\infty E(1_{t < X}) dt =\int_0^\infty P(t < X)dt 
X\geqslant0\implies X=\int_0^X\,\mathrm dt=\int_0^\infty\mathbf 1_{X\gt t}\,\mathrm dt
